name: Homemade Goldfish Treats
author: Daphne Pruitt
summary: Spice up your day with some flavorful cheese crackers! Wonderful cheese taste with not a lot of ingredients!
ingredients: ¼ cup butter, cut into cubes
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese, flour, butter, and salt in a food processor; pulse until dough is consistency of course sand
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough is moistened
Wrap dough in plastic wrap and refrigerate for 20 minutes
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Line a baking sheet with parchment paper
Roll dough onto a lightly floured work surface and cut into desired shapes using a cookie cutter
If you choose to use a fish cut-out, use a toothpick to make faces
Arrange shapes on the prepared baking sheet
Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown and crispy, 15 to 16 minutes
